   <div class="row">
      <div class="span12 democracy_prep lead">
         <h2>About our kids</h2>
         12 high school students from Democracy Prep Charter School 
         in Harlem will be selected to spend the afternoon with the 
         hackers of angelHack. Our kids are sophomores and juniors with 
         curiosity and passion for software development, but who have no 
         access to computer science courses at school. 
      </div>
      <div class="span12 democracy_prep lead">
         <h2>We need your team!</h2>
         What you can expect: a student will shadow your team for a 
         couple of hours while you're working on your hack. They'll be 
         there to observe only, <em>not to pester you</em>. By hosting 
         a student for the afternoon, you'll be giving them a window into 
         a future they can get excited about. 
         <br/><br/>
      </div>
      <div class="span12 democracy_prep lead">
         <h2>To qualify you must:</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="span4 democracy_prep lead">
         <img src="img/glyphicons_043_group.png" alt="" > Have a team of 3+ people
      </div>
      <div class="span4 democracy_prep lead">
         <img src="img/glyphicons_206_ok_2.png" alt="" > Be registered for angelHack
      </div>
      <div class="span4 democracy_prep lead">
         <img src="img/glyphicons_012_heart.png" alt="" > Not be creepy or a jerk
      </div>
